the largest on record dating back to 1990, according to Bloomberg News. [AFP] Vanguard News Nigeria China's exports expanded more than expected last month as key markets eased virus containment measures, official data showed Monday, but imports unexpectedly shrank despite a push to boost domestic demand. Overseas shipments have been hit less than feared by the pandemic, thanks to global demand for medical supplies but economists… September 7, 2020 In "Foreign" The National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) said the value of the total trade at the end of 2016 was N17. 35 billion. March 7, 2017 In "Business" The National Bureau of Statistics (NBS), said the country recorded a total trade value of N32.26 trillion year-on-year in 2018, representing 39.3 per cent increase over the corresponding period in 2017. March 3, 2019 In "News"